Two pointer approach: uses tow pointer (left,right) left++.right--

USED WHEN:- Min/max,count,search,sum,pair,reverse array,palindrome... keyword you find.

Example:-Reverse an array
int arr[] = {1,2,3,4,5};
int n = 5;

int l = 0;
int r = n - 1;

while(l < r){
    swap(arr[l], arr[r]);
    l++;
    r--;
}


Example2:- palindrome checking
string s = "madam";
int l = 0, r = s.size()-1;
bool ok = true;

while(l < r){
   if(s[l] != s[r]){
      ok = false;
      break;
   }
   l++;
   r--;
}


